{"id":"301870808_State_Complexity_and_the_Monoid_of_Transformations_of_a_Finite_Set","abstract":"In this paper we consider the state complexity of an operation on formal languages, root(L). This naturally entails the discussion of the monoid of transformations of a finite set. We obtain good upper and lower bounds on the state complexity of root(L) over alphabets of all sizes.","authors":["Bryan Krawetz","John Lawrence","Jeffery Shallit"],"meta":["June 2003"],"references":["221212227_On_Deterministic_Finite_Automata_and_Syntactic_Monoid_Size_Continued","221212152_Roots_and_Powers_of_Regular_Languages","268679745_On_a_generalization_of_permutations_Some_properties_of_transformations","268542724_On_the_maximal_order_in_S_n_and_S_n","268247495_On_Transformations_Transformation-Semigroups_and_Graphs","247931052_The_Maximum_Order_of_an_Element_of_a_Finite_Symmetric_Group","246997731_On_basic_groups_for_the_set_of_functions_over_a_finite_domain","239061519_Algorithmic_Number_Theory_Volume_1","234794903_On_the_state_complexity_of_intersection_of_regular_languages","228057764_Introduction_To_Automata_Theory_Languages_And_Computation","222624880_The_state_complexities_of_some_basic_operations_on_regular_languages","222499415_Automata_Boolean_Matrices_and_Ultimate_Periodicity","220520656_State_Complexity_of_Regular_Languages","220180337_State_complexity_and_the_monoid_of_transformations_of_a_finite_set","220148495_Composition_sequences_for_functions_over_a_finite_domain","220148412_On_deterministic_finite_automata_and_syntactic_monoid_size"]}